  "title": "Eleanor's Story: Life After War",
  "description": "Ingrid Garner, 16X award-winning creator of \"Eleanor’s Story: An American Girl in Hitler’s Germany\", delivers a fascinating sequel to her grandmother’s acclaimed memoir. In 1946, teen Eleanor finally returns home from WWII Berlin but struggles to navigate U.S. high school while haunted by war memories. ★★★★★ – Edmonton Journal",
  "credits": "<strong>Playwright</strong>: Ingrid Garner<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: Ingrid Garner<br/><strong>Designers</strong>: Noelle Sammour - Sound<br/><strong>Stage Manager</strong>: Julia Bueneman<br/>",
  "website": "https://eleanorsstory.com",
  "plain_language": "In this powerful sequel to Eleanor’s Story, Ingrid Garner shares the true story of her grandmother returning to America in 1946 after surviving WWII in Berlin. Safe at last, teenage Eleanor struggles to fit in with classmates who can’t understand what she’s been through.",
